WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:05.661
<i>Theorizing that one could time travel
within his own lifetime,</i>

00:05.739 --> 00:08.674
<i>Dr. Sam Beckett stepped
into the Quantum Leap accelerator...</i>

00:08.742 --> 00:10.733
<i>and vanished.</i>

00:15.315 --> 00:17.943
<i>He awoke to find himself
trapped in the past,</i>

00:18.018 --> 00:21.545
<i>facing mirror images
that were not his own...</i>

00:21.621 --> 00:26.854
<i>and driven by an unknown force
to change history for the better.</i>

00:26.926 --> 00:32.192
<i>His only guide on this journey is Al,
an observer from his own time,</i>

00:32.265 --> 00:36.634
<i>who appears in the form of a hologram
that only Sam can see and hear.</i>

00:36.703 --> 00:40.867
<i>And so, Dr. Beckett finds himself
leaping from life to life,</i>

00:40.940 --> 00:43.875
<i>striving to put right
what once went wrong...</i>

00:43.943 --> 00:47.276
<i>and hoping each time
that his next leap...</i>

00:47.347 --> 00:49.338
<i>will be the leap home.</i>

00:51.284 --> 00:57.120
<i>Dr. Flanagan report to Emergency.
Dr. Flanagan-</i>

00:57.190 --> 01:00.626
Can you hear him?
He's out there! Who?

01:00.693 --> 01:03.856
Charlie! He's comin' over the
wire! He's gonna kill us all!

01:03.930 --> 01:07.058
<i>We gotta get outta here! He's
gonna cut our heads off! Baxter.!</i>

01:09.602 --> 01:14.096
I warned you about acting crazy on my
floor, didn't I? Trough "A"! Trough "A"!

01:14.174 --> 01:17.507
I guess I'm gonna have
to teach you a lesson.

01:17.577 --> 01:19.807
Now don't you fight me,
or I'll break your freakin' neck.

01:19.879 --> 01:22.780
- Hey, that isn't necessary, is it?
- Sam, don't get up.

01:22.849 --> 01:24.817
- Why not?
- Just don't get up.

01:24.884 --> 01:28.149
<i>I can't breathe. My arm.! Stop it.!
Charlie's comin'! Oh, you can't breathe, huh?</i>

01:28.221 --> 01:33.420
<i>- Charlie's comin'!
- You can't get up, because you don't have any legs.</i>

01:35.929 --> 01:37.863
Oh, boy.

